Why CloudROC Managed Service for DevOps Toolchains – Benefits

Cost savings through a single platform for the integrated DevOps Toolchains

The toolchains are deployed into a single namespace of the cluster for a tenant.

Elasticity

Deployed as cloud native applications to enable auto-scaling of the toolchain applications.

Built on open standard

Use the most popular open source tools. No single vendor lock-in.

Security

DevSecOps principles, security scanning and security patching is performed regularly. The security policy on the user access management and API access follows the security and compliance requirement.

Hybrid multi-cloud

Both SaaS and managed services models are offered: for the hosting services, the customers can subscribe to the services as needed. For the managed services, customers can have the multi-cloud platforms built for your different application teams and environments.

SLA Guarantee

High availability architecture for 99.9% of the service availability.

Solution At a Glance

Cloudroc DevOps Cloud services provides an end to end life cycle of DevSecOps toolchain services for the software delivery and operations value chain – from plan, code, build, test, release, deploy, operate and monitor to security.

Agile Project Management Services

Built on Redmine & Kanban

Redmine

A free and open source, web-based project management and issue tracking tool.
Benefits

  • Manage multiple projects and associated subprojects
  • Project wikis and forums
  • Flexible, role-based access control

Feature Description

Use Cases

  • Turn Redmine into an Agile project management tool
  • Manage time tracking, resource management and reporting
  • Integrate Redmine with code repository
  • Start Helpdesk in Redmine
  • Prepare estimates and invoices

Benefits

  • Better visibility. Visualization is an important Kanban practice, and the most recognizable feature of the method is the Kanban board
  • Improved efficiency
  • Increased productivity
  • Preventing team overburden
  • Increased team focus
  • Reduced waste
  • Flexibility
  • Improved collaboration

Feature Description

Use Cases

  • Hosting your project management platform
  • Integrated Project management portal for the software projects
  • Supporting Agile project management
  • Manage issues, activities, time tracking, resource management and reporting
  • Integrate Redmine with Git and Jenkins

Kanban Board

A Kanban board is a tool for workflow visualization and a key component of the Kanban method. Visualizing your workflow and tasks on a Kanban board helps you better understand your processes and gain an overview of your workload.

Jenkins

Benefits

Integrated Testing Services

Built on SonarQube & Selenium

SonarQube

Code Quality Assurance tool that collects and analyzes source code, and provides reports for the code quality of your project. It combines static and dynamic analysis tools and enables quality to be measured continually over time.
Benefits

  • Improve the quality of your code using static analysis techniques
  • Reports on duplicated code, coding standards
  • Detect Bugs. Code Smells. Security Vulnerabilities
  • Record metrics history and provides evolution graphs

How It Works

Use Cases

  • Do code Quality Assurance
  • Collects and analyzes source code
  • Provides reports for the code quality by combining static and dynamic analysis tools and enables quality to be measured continually over time

Benefits

  • Faster Feedback Cycle. Without test automation, feedback for newly developed features can take a while
  • Team Saves Time
  • Reduced Business Expenses
  • Higher Test Coverage.
  • Reusability of Test Suite
  • Faster Time to Market
  • Better Insights
  • Improved Accuracy

How It Works

Use Cases

  • Workflow based automatic triggering of both manual and automated test cases
  • Enables execution of Test Script in any host from central location
  • Synchronization of test artifacts with development and delivery cycles helps project teams to achieve Continuous Integration and Continuous Delivery
  • Manages all of your automated Selenium scripts, schedules tests to run simultaneously on remote hosts, and generates Run Reports

App Security Services

Built on Vault and SecureCodeBox

Vault

Benefits

  • Secure Secret Storage: Arbitrary key/value secrets, sensitive environment variables, database credentials, API keys, etc
  • Dynamic Secrets: Vault can generate secrets on-demand for some systems, such as AWS or SQL databases
  • Data Encryption: Vault can encrypt and decrypt data without storing it

How It Works

Use Cases

  • A centralized place to manage account permissions and secrets
  • Generate secrets on-demand and API Key Generation for Scripts
  • Encrypt and decrypt data to allow applications to encrypt their data while still storing it in the primary data store

Benefits

  • Easy Use in Cloud Based Projects
  • CLI First
  • Cascading Scans

Feature Description

Use Cases

  • For Dev-Teams: Scan your applications to identify low-hanging fruit issues in an early stage during the development process and free the resources of pen-testers to concentrate on major security issues
  • For Ops-Teams: Orchestrate and perform continuous and automated routine scans of your applications in the live environment and thereby reduce vulnerability risks
  • For Security-Teams: Use the secureCodeBox to run security scans on large-scale networks and identify vulnerabilities alongside your organization’s infrastructure.

SecureCodeBox

ITSM Workflow Incident Management

Dispatch is a crisis management orchestration framework that manages incident metadata and resources.

Dispatch

Benefits

  • The incident commander no longer needs to manage access to resources or multiple data streams
  • Communications are standardized (both in style and interval) across incidents
  • Incident participants are automatically engaged based on the type, priority, and description of the incident
  • Incident tasks are tracked and owners are reminded if they’re not completed on time
  • All incident data is centrally tracked
  • A common API is provided for internal users and tools

Workflow

Use Cases

  • Resource Management — The management of not only data collected about the incident itself but all of the metadata about the response
  • Individual Engagement — Understanding the best way to engage individuals and teams, and doing so based on incident context
  • Life Cycle Management — Providing the Incident Commander (IC) tools to easily manage the life cycle of the incident
  • Incident Learning — Building on past incidents to speed up the resolution of future incidents

Observability Services

Built on OpenTelemetry, Prometheus and Grafana

Prometheus

Benefits

  • Monitor highly dynamic container environments
  • Allows fast outage discovery
  • A monitoring solution that gathers time-series based numerical data
  • Provides a functional query language, PromQL, that allows us to select and aggregate time-series data in real-time

Workflow

Use Cases

  • Container infrastructure monitoring
  • Group, suppress, and silence alerts as needed
  • Route alerts to the right receiver integration, like email or other tools you're using
  • Works with exporters that can take data from various sources and translate it into metrics that this tool can collect and display

Benefits

  • Feature-rich Customizable dashboards
  • Visualization tools such as heatmaps, histograms, and charts
  • Native support of a broad range of databases

Workflow

Use Cases

  • Analytics and interactive visualization web application
  • Provides charts, graphs, and alerts for the web when connected to supported data sources
